author: gstein
msg: Unroll some function call nesting related to merge_file() which also
simplifies some argument lists (that were merely passed down to the next
function).
Corrected passing of log_accum to a ** pointer so that lower layers can
properly alloc/assign the accumulator.
Removed extraneous passing of left/right_version which were always NULL.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/update_editor.c:
(merge_props): LOG_ACCUM should be ** so lower layers can assign it.
removed LOCK_STATE, LAST_CHANGE, and LEFT/RIGHT_VERSION as they are no
longer needed. removed computation of ENTRY_PROPS. pass correct
LOG_ACCUM to svn_wc__merge_props, and hardcode NULL for the LEFT/
RIGHT_VERSION arguments. remove the ENTRY_PROPS handling, as the
caller will handle those properties.
(loggy_tweak_base_node): LOG_ACCUM is ** so lower layers can assign to
it, and correct its passing to svn_wc__loggy_entry_modify().
(merge_file): remove the (now-unused) PROP_STATE, LOCK_STATE,
NEW_BASE_PROPS, NEW_ACTUAL_PROPS, and LAST_CHANGE parameters. added a
new LOCK_REMOVED input parameter to indicate when a lock is removed
from the node. remove the calls to loggy_tweak_base_node and
merge_props, in deference to the caller managing that.
(close_file): pull the LAST_CHANGE and LOCK_STATE handling up and out of
the merge_file call chain. bring the calls to loggy_tweak_base_node
and merge_props here, too, and adjust various parameter sets.
